    </div>

    <p>The immune benefits of vitamin C extend beyond cold prevention. Vitamin C concentrates in immune cells at levels 10 to 100 times higher than blood plasma, indicating its critical role in immune cell function. It supports the production and activity of white blood cells (neutrophils, lymphocytes), enhances the skin barrier as the body's first line of defense, and acts as a potent antioxidant that protects immune cells from oxidative damage during the inflammatory response to infection.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
